  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chicken thigh fillets</strong> and cook for 3-4 min, turning once half way, until they're golden on both sides</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sun-dried tomatoes</strong> to a bowl, cover them with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and leave them to soak</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice&nbsp;the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomatoes</strong>&nbsp;into wedges</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> are golden, transfer them to a plate, leaving any juices behind&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min over a medium-low heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> tomato wedges</strong>, <strong>sun-dried tomatoes</strong> (including the soaking liquid), half of the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min</p>\r\n<p>Return the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> to the pan, cover with a lid and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Re-boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving a cup&nbsp;of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Shave the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> with a peeler until you end up with a pile of 'cheese shavings' and grate any remaining <strong>cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl - this is your<strong> balsamic dressing</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>chicken</strong> is cooked through, shred it<strong>&nbsp;</strong>apart in the pan, using two forks - this technique is known as &lsquo;pulling'</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> black olives</strong> and <strong>chopped basil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and add the drained<strong> linguine&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: if the sauce looks a bit dry add some of the starchy pasta water&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sun-dried-tomato-and-olive-chicken-pasta/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash and dry&nbsp;the <strong>rocket</strong>&nbsp;then tumble it&nbsp;with the<strong>&nbsp;cheese shavings</strong> and the<strong> balsamic dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Serve the<strong> fresh tomato &amp; chicken ragu</strong>&nbsp;and garnish with the remaining&nbsp;<strong>grated cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
